{
  "id": "helix-pnpm-migration",
  "title": "Migrate from npm workspaces to pnpm",
  "category": "infrastructure",
  "description": "Migrate the Helix monorepo from npm to pnpm for better Turborepo integration, stricter dependency isolation, and faster installs.\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Install pnpm globally and generate `pnpm-workspace.yaml` from current npm workspaces config in `package.json`\n2. Remove `workspaces` field from root `package.json`\n3. Update `packageManager` field to pnpm version\n4. Delete `package-lock.json`, run `pnpm install` to generate `pnpm-lock.yaml`\n5. Update `turbo.json` â€” add `packageManager: \"pnpm\"` if needed\n6. Update all GitHub Actions workflows: replace `npm ci` with `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, add pnpm setup step\n7. Update `engines` field in root `package.json` to add pnpm version requirement\n8. Update `CONTRIBUTING.md` with pnpm installation and usage instructions\n9. Remove `package-lock.json` from git tracking, add to `.gitignore` if not already\n10. Update all internal cross-workspace scripts that use `npm run --workspace=...` to `pnpm --filter=...`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `pnpm-lock.yaml` exists, `package-lock.json` is gone\n- All CI workflows pass with pnpm\n- `turbo dev`, `turbo build`, `turbo test` all work\n- `npm run build:mcp-servers` equivalent works with pnpm filter syntax",
  "status": "done",
  "priority": 4,
